ergarten in italy before graduating stuttgart american high school he received a bachelors degree from the university of notre dame in government and liberal studies in  an mba from the johnson graduate school of management at cornell university in  and masters of science from the mit sloan school of management as a sloan fellow in  in telecommunicationsedit attedit he spent  years at att where he started out as an intern from – he was president and ceo of att network systems international based in the netherlands he launched the online divisions att worldnet service in february  which introduced unlimited internet dial up for month as long as you subscribed to atts long distance services in may  he became head of att wireless terabeam corporationedit from march  to june  he was ceo and chairman of terabeam corporation embarq corporationedit in june  hesse joined sprint and oversaw the spinoff of its landline service – embarq corporation sprintedit on december   he became ceo of sprint nextel during his tenure he appeared in numerous television commercials for the company filmed in black and white and created by goodby silverstein  partners the ads were filmed in new york city when hesse took over at sprint the company was losing numerous customers his strategy to stem further losses included improved customer service an increased emphasis on prepaid cell phones striking a deal with apple to sell iphones and other apple products and a g presence investmentownership stake in wimaxprovider clearwire he also started adding retail stores across the nation in an attempt for increased inperson customer service on august   sprint announced that hesse would be replaced by marcelo claure founder of brightstar corporation personal lifeedit dan hesse took a year off of work following him leaving sprint hesse never really endorsed any political candidates but he did talk with mitt romney during his time campaigning for the  united states presidential elections referencesedit  s