bly old human grieflet it all be painlet it all be suffering let it be wretchedbut not this one sweet hour in the summerand not the fragrance of the red cloverand not the deep tender pleasurein my soul” the novel attracted especially young veterans of the ww i and reflected hesses personal crisis and interest in jungian psychoanalysis with aldous huxley he shared belief in the need for spiritual selfrealization there is no reality except the one contained within us hesse once said that is why so many people live such an unreal life they take the images outside them for reality and never allow the world within to assert itself hesse later admitted that demian was a story of individuation in the jungian manner httpwwwkirjastoscifihhessehtm steppenwolf plot summaryit is a discourse of a man who believes himself to be of two natures one high the spiritual nature of man while the other is low animalistic a wolf of the steppes this man is entangled in an irresolvable struggle never content with either nature because he cannot see beyond this selfmade concepthttpenwikipediaorgwikisteppenwolfnovelplotsummary siddartha plot summarythe story begins as siddhartha the son of a brahmin leaves his home to join the ascetics with his companion govinda the two set out in the search of enlightenmentsiddhartha goes from asceticism to a very worldly life as a trader with a lover and back to asceticism as he attempts to achieve this goalthe story takes place in ancient india around the time of gautama buddha likely between the fourth and seventh centuries bchttpenwikipediaorgwikisiddharthanovelfilmversions the glass bead game plot summarythe glass bead game takes place at an unspecified date centuries into the future hesse suggested that he imagined the books narrator writing around the start of the th century the setting is a fictional province of central europe called castalia reserved by political decision for the life of the mind technology and economic life are kept to a strict minimum castalia is home to an austere order of intellectuals with a twofold mission to run boarding schools for boys and to nurture and play the glass bead game whose exact nature remains elusive and whose devotees occupy a special school within castalia known as waldzell the rules of the game are only alluded to and are so sophisticated that they are not easy to imagine playing the game well requires years of hard study of music mathematics and cultural history essentially the game is an abstract synthesis of all arts and sciences it proceeds by players making deep connections between seemingly unrelated topicshttpenwikipediaorgwikitheglassbeadgame demian plot summaryemil sinclair is a young boy raised in a bourgeois home amidst what is described as a scheinwelt a play on words that means world of light as well as world of illusion emils entire existence can be summarized as a struggle between two worlds the show world of illusion related to the hindu concept of maya and the real world the world of spiritual truth in the course of the novel accompanied and prompted by his mysterious classmate max demian he detaches from and revolts against the superficial ideals of the world of appearances and eventually awakens into a realization of selfhttpenwikipediaorgwikidemian hermann hesse is an important person to the th century because he explores the journey to understanding life and reaching the ultimate goal in the human condition he is an intelligent person who discovers and expresses the meaning of life through ficticious characters in his novels works citeddemian wikipedia the free encyclopedia web  feb  httpenwikipediaorgwikidemianthe glass bead game wikipedia the free encyclopedia web  feb  httpenwikipediaorgwikitheglassbeadgamehermann hesse  a short biography alles über hermann hesse  all about hermann hesse web  feb  httpwwwhermannhessecomhtmlenglishebiographiehtmlhermann hesse wikipedia the free encyclopedia  feb  web  feb  httpenwikipediaorgwikihermannhesseinflue